  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then reduce the heat to low and cook for 8-10 min or until the onion has softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683627542618-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683627542618-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683627542618-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683627542618-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683627542618-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half, lengthways</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden</p><p>Top, tail and slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) into discs</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683627546005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683627546005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683627546005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683627546005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683627546005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and cut into 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>square per person</p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pastry square[s]</strong> to the tray[s] and score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683627551238-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683627551238-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683627551238-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683627551238-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683627551238-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Prick the inside of the border all over with a fork (this will stop you getting a soggy bottom!)</p><p>Top the pastry square evenly with the <strong>caramelised onion</strong> and <strong>courgette discs </strong>and drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 10 min or until the pastry is golden and the edges have started to puff up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683627554763-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683627554763-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683627554763-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683627554763-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683627554763-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tart[s] has had an initial 10 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and dollop over your <strong>plant based ‘Nduja</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!), then top with your <strong>pine nuts </strong>and return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 5 min or until the pine nuts are golden and the pastry is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p><p>Once cooked through and golden, remove the tray[s] from the oven and drizzle over the <strong>agave </strong>– this is your <strong>plant-based 'Nduja, caramelised onion & courgette tart</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
